%p
  Delaware’s “Civil Union and Equality Act of 2011,” S.B. 30, would allow same-gender couples to have the rights and responsibilities on the state level that accrue to opposite-sex marriage. You can see the bill and its status at
  %a{:href => "http://legis.delaware.gov/LIS/LIS146.nsf/vwLegislation/SB+30?Opendocument"} http://legis.delaware.gov/LIS/LIS146.nsf/vwLegislation/SB+30?Opendocument
%p
  The bill has passed the Senate and will soon be considered by the House.
